The paper discusses cooperative communications in multi-antenna relay networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The paper also considers the large scale fading characteristics of the network, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of relaying protocols to improve spectral efficiency, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM) systems.
